-- People's Bank Chief Zhou Says Easier for Banks to `Lean Against the Wind'
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2010-10-11T18:42:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/people-s-bank-chief-zhou-says-easier-for-banks-to-lean-against-the-wind-.html
China’s central bank Governor Zhou
Xiaochuan said central banks should “lean against the wind” to
prevent asset-price bubbles.  “If a price of an asset rises too fast we try to have a
policy to deal with that,” Zhou said in Washington. “A
relatively easier task for a central bank is to lean against the
wind.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
